      • bulkDeleteMessages

        void bulkDeleteMessages(boolean throwEx,
                        java.util.List<IMessage> messages)
        Build delete a collection of messages.
        Parameters:
        throwEx - If true, the the event will check and throw exceptions. If false, the exceptions below will be ignored.
        messages - The messages to delete.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If this channel is a private channel.
        PermissionException - If the identity does not have Manage Messages permission.
        ErrorResponseException - If one of the messages is not from this channel.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If one of the messages is older than 2 weeks.
        See Also:
        ErrorResponse.UNKNOWN_MESSAGE

      • removeReaction

        void removeReaction(IMember member,
                    java.lang.String messageId,
                    java.lang.String unicode)
        Remove a member's reaction from a message.
        Parameters:
        member - The member that reacted on the message.
        messageId - The message's ID.
        unicode - The unicode reaction.
        Throws:
        PermissionException - If the reaction to remove is not reacted by the identity itself, and the identity does not have Manager Messages permission.
        HigherHierarchyException -
        • If the member is the server owner.
        • If the member is at a higher or same hierarchy as the identity.
        ErrorResponseException - If the reaction is not found from the message's reactions.
        See Also:
        ErrorResponse.UNKNOWN_EMOJI
